# EDB Documentation 

> Comprehensive documentation for EDB (EnterpriseDB) products, Postgres tools, and cloud-native database solutions.

> Full site: https://www.enterprisedb.com/docs/

The markdown source for any page under https://www.enterprisedb.com/docs/ can be retrieved by appending ".md" or ".mdx" to the end of the URL. Each markdown file is MDX: it begins with a YAML frontmatter block that contains at minimum a `title` field, typically a `navigation` list of child-page filenames, and an optional `description`, followed by the main content in Markdown/MDX. Navigation entries and some hyperlinks in the content are relative paths; to construct the full URL for any such link, resolve it against the page's own URL and then append '.md' to get the markdown (e.g., the navigation entry `quickstart` on the page `https://www.enterprisedb.com/docs/pgd/latest/` becomes `https://www.enterprisedb.com/docs/pgd/latest/quickstart.md`).

The rest of this page is a generated index of the root topics for all products and guides, organized by product and version, with links to the first subsection topics for the latest version of each product.

